title: Jarryd Hayne may be out of Auckland Nines
text:
Jarryd Hayne may be out of Auckland Nines DAVID LONG Last updated 11:47, February 5 2017 Anthony Au-Yeung 
Jarryd Hayne may not play again in this year's Auckland Nines. 
After Shaun Johnson missed the first day of action, this year's Auckland Nines might have suffered another blow, with Jarryd Hayne not expected to play on Sunday. 
While there is no official word from the Titans, it is understood that the former San Francisco 49ers running back has a swollen knee and team management have taken the precautionary measure of resting him for the rest of the day. 
Hayne didn't play in the Titans' 22-4 loss to the Panthers on Sunday morning, but as his team had already qualified for the quarterfinals by winning both of their games on Saturday, he was never going to be used in a meaningless fixture as there are potentially three more games to be played if the Titans make it to the final.
